\title{Modelica}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Modelica acausal equation-based multi-domain modeling via Wolfram Language. Chemputation-native simulation with automatic conservation laws. Lambda-Modelica bridge for string diagram semantics. Fixed point classification for 3-coloring/3-MATCH systems."}

\subtree{
\title{Modelica Skill: Acausal Multi-Domain Modeling}
\p{\strong{Status}: ✅ Production Ready + Triplet #2 + Lambda Bridge + Fixed Point Classification \strong{Trit}: 0 (ERGODIC - coordinator) \strong{Color}: #26D826 (Green) \strong{Principle}: Constraints over causality + Stochastic Equilibrium Verification + String Diagram Semantics \strong{Frame}: $0 = F(x, y, t)$ constraint satisfaction + Fokker-Planck convergence + Lambda↔Modelica bridge}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{\strong{Modelica} is the \strong{chemputation-native} modeling language. Unlike imperative programming ($y = f(x)$), Modelica defines \strong{constraints} that the solver satisfies—directly analogous to thermodynamic settling and reaction-diffusion equilibria.}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Acausal Semantics}: Equations, not assignments}
\li{\strong{Conservation Laws}: Automatic Kirchhoff at connectors}
\li{\strong{Multi-Domain}: Electrical, mechanical, fluid, thermal unified}
\li{\strong{DAE Solving}: Differential-algebraic equations with index reduction}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Framework}
\subtree{
\title{Wolfram Language API (Modern v11.3+)}
\pre{\startverb
(* Import and explore *)
model = SystemModel["Modelica.Electrical.Analog.Examples.ChuaCircuit"];
model["Description"]
model["Diagram"]
model["SystemEquations"]

(* Simulate *)
sim = SystemModelSimulate[model, 100];
SystemModelPlot[sim, {"C1.v", "C2.v"}]

(* Create from equations *)
CreateSystemModel["MyModel", {
  x''[t] + 2*zeta*omega*x'[t] + omega^2*x[t] == F[t]
}, t, <|
  "ParameterValues" -> {omega -> 1, zeta -> 0.1},
  "InitialValues" -> {x -> 0, x' -> 0}
|>]

(* Connect components *)
ConnectSystemModelComponents[
  {"R" ∈ "Modelica.Electrical.Analog.Basic.Resistor",
   "C" ∈ "Modelica.Electrical.Analog.Basic.Capacitor",
   "V" ∈ "Modelica.Electrical.Analog.Sources.SineVoltage"},
  {"V.p" -> "R.p", "R.n" -> "C.p", "C.n" -> "V.n"}
]

(* Linearize for control design *)
eq = FindSystemModelEquilibrium[model];
ss = SystemModelLinearize[model, eq];  (* Returns StateSpaceModel *)
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{1. Acausal vs Causal (Chemputation Alignment)}
\pre{\startverb
| Paradigm | Semantics | Example |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| **Causal (von Neumann)** | $y = f(x)$ | `output = function(input)` |
| **Acausal (Modelica)** | $0 = F(x, y, t)$ | `v = R * i` (bidirectional) |
\stopverb}

\p{Modelica's acausal nature means:}

\ul{
\li{Equations define relationships, not data flow}
\li{Solver determines causality at compile time}
\li{Same model works in multiple contexts}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Connector Semantics (Conservation Laws)}
\pre{\startverb
        effort (voltage v)
Port A ──────────────────── Port B
        ←─── flow (current i) ───→
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Connection equations} (automatic):}

\ul{
\li{Effort variables \strong{equalized}: $v_A = v_B$}
\li{Flow variables \strong{sum to zero}: $\startverb \sum\stopverb i = 0$ (Kirchhoff)}
}

\pre{\startverb
| Domain | Effort | Flow | Conservation |
|--------|--------|------|--------------|
| Electrical | Voltage $v$ | Current $i$ | $\sum i = 0$ |
| Translational | Position $s$ | Force $F$ | $\sum F = 0$ |
| Rotational | Angle $\phi$ | Torque $\tau$ | $\sum \tau = 0$ |
| Thermal | Temperature $T$ | Heat flow $\dot{Q}$ | Energy conservation |
| Fluid | Pressure $p$, enthalpy $h$ | Mass flow $\dot{m}$ | Mass/energy conservation |
\stopverb}
}

